        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
            A federal immigration raid in two Southern California cannabis farms
            resulted in the detention of 319 undocumented individuals, including
            14 minors. One farm worker died from injuries sustained during the
            operation. Federal agents were accused of using unreasonable force,
            including deploying smoke canisters and projectiles.
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
            Federal officials, including Homeland Security Secretary Kristi Noem
            and border czar Tom Homan,
